18#include "ODEAN13Writer.h"
19#include "ODUPCEANCommon.h"
20#include "ODWriterHelper.h"
21
22#include <array>
23#include <vector>
24
25namespace ZXing {
26namespace OneD {
27
28static const int FIRST_DIGIT_ENCODINGS[] = {
29 0x00, 0x0B, 0x0D, 0xE, 0x13, 0x19, 0x1C, 0x15, 0x16, 0x1A
30};
31
32static const int CODE_WIDTH = 3 + // start guard
33 (7 * 6) + // left bars
34 5 + // middle guard
35 (7 * 6) + // right bars
36 3; // end guard
37
38BitMatrix
39EAN13Writer::encode(const std::wstring& contents, int width, int height) const
40{
41 auto digits = UPCEANCommon::DigitString2IntArray<13>(contents);
42
43 int parities = FIRST_DIGIT_ENCODINGS[digits[0]];
44 std::vector<bool> result(CODE_WIDTH, false);
45 int pos = 0;
46
47 pos += WriterHelper::AppendPattern(result, pos, UPCEANCommon::START_END_PATTERN, true);
48
49 // See {@link #EAN13Reader} for a description of how the first digit & left bars are encoded
50 for (int i = 1; i <= 6; i++) {
51 int digit = digits[i];
52 if ((parities >> (6 - i) & 1) == 1) {
53 digit += 10;
54 }
55 pos += WriterHelper::AppendPattern(result, pos, UPCEANCommon::L_AND_G_PATTERNS[digit], false);
56 }
57
58 pos += WriterHelper::AppendPattern(result, pos, UPCEANCommon::MIDDLE_PATTERN, false);
59
60 for (int i = 7; i <= 12; i++) {
61 pos += WriterHelper::AppendPattern(result, pos, UPCEANCommon::L_PATTERNS[digits[i]], true);
62 }
63 WriterHelper::AppendPattern(result, pos, UPCEANCommon::START_END_PATTERN, true);
64 return WriterHelper::RenderResult(result, width, height, _sidesMargin >= 0 ? _sidesMargin : 9);
65}
66
67} // OneD
68} // ZXing
